 Production Agriculture, 6, pp. 181-190; Follett, R.F., Kimble, J.M., Lal, R., The potential of U.S. grazing lands to sequester soil carbon (2001) The Potential of U.S. Grazing Lands to Sequester Carbon and Mitigate the Greenhouse Effect, pp. 401-430. , R.F. Follett, J.M. Kimble and R. Lal (editors). Sleeping Bear Press Inc. Chelsea, Mich; Follett, R.F., Samson-Liebig, S.E., Kimble, J.M., Pruessner, E.G., Waltman, S.W., Carbon sequestration under the Conservation Reserve Program in the historic grassland soils of the United States of America (2001) Soil Carbon Sequestration and the Greenhouse Effect, pp. 27-40. , R. Lal (editor). Soil Science Society of America Special Publication 57. Soil Science Society of America. Madison, Wis; Franzluebbers, A.J., Hons, F.M., Zuberer, D.A., In situ and potential CO2 evolution from a Fluventic Ustochrept in southcentral Texas as affected by tillage and cropping intensity (1998) Soil and Tillage Research, 47, pp. 303-308; Franzleubbers, A.J., Stuedemann, J.A., Schomberg, H.H., Wilkinson, S.R., Soil organic C and N pools under long-term pasture management in the Southern Piedmont USA (2000) Soil Biology and Biochemistry, 32, pp. 469-478; Frye, W.W., Blevins, R.L., Soil organic matter under long-term no-tillage and conventional tillage corn production in Kentucky (1997) Soil Organic Matter in Temperate Agroecosystems: Long-term Experiments in North America, pp. 227-234. , E.A. Paul, K. Paustian, E.T. Elliott and C.V. Cole (editors). CRC Press. Boca Raton, Fla. 414 pp; Gebhart, D.L., Johnson, H.B., Mayeux, H.S., Polley, H.W., The CRP increases soil organic matter (1994) Journal of Soil and Water Conservation, 49, pp. 488-492; Huggins, D.R., Allan, D.L., Gradner, J.C., Karlen, D.L., Bezdicek, D.F., Alms, M.J., Flock, M., Staben, M.L., Enhancing carbon sequestration in CRP-managed land (1998) Management of Carbon Sequestration in Soil, pp. 323-350. , R. Lal, J.M. Kimble, R.F. Follett and B.A. Stewart (editors). CRC Press. Boca Raton, F